    <statement><p>Add or subtract the rational expressions to a single rational expression and then simplify. If applicable, state the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{x}{x-9}-\frac{7x+18}{x^{2}-9x}} =}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{x+2}{x}, x\ne 9</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{x}{x-9}-\frac{7x+18}{x^{2}-9x}} 
      \amp = {\frac{x}{x-9}}-\frac{{7x+18}}{x(x - 9)} \\
      \amp = \frac{x \cdot x}{({x-9}) \cdot x}-\frac{{7x+18}}{x(x - 9)} \\
      \amp = \frac{x^{2}}{x(x - 9)}-\frac{{7x+18}}{x(x - 9)} \\
      \amp = \frac{x^{2}-({7x+18})}{x(x - 9)} \\
      \amp = \frac{{x^{2}-7x-18}}{x(x - 9)} \\
      \amp = \frac{(x - 9)(x+2)}{x(x - 9)} \\
      \amp = {\frac{x+2}{x}, x\ne 9}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>{x-9}</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>x \ne {9}</m>.</p>
</solution>
